The memorandum is a delegation of authority from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Secretary of State. It grants the Secretary of State the authority to determine whether it is in the security interests of the United States to provide approximately $128 million in assistance to Ukraine, without being constrained by any provision of law. Additionally, the memorandum grants the Secretary of State the authority to direct the drawdown of approximately $128 million in defense articles and services from the Department of Defense, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. The memorandum concludes by authorizing the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.